{
  "texts": [
    "Robust optimization methods work by modifying the objective or constraints to model the possible variation in the data.",
    "One very successful application of robust optimization is in robust control, where a control system is designed so that the control performance is not too sensitive to changes in the system dynamics [ZD98, KDG96].",
    "So-called linear quadratic optimal control was developed around 1960, and used in many applications.",
    "Its occasional sensitivity to the data (in this case, the dynamic model of the system being controlled) was noted then; by the early 1990s robust control methods were developed, and are now very widely used.",
    "Regularization."
  ]
}